25/06/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- The ruling Justice and Development Party (AKP) unveiled its campaign promises Sunday (June 24th), ahead of the July 22nd parliamentary elections. 
The party is pledging an entirely new constitution, under which the parliamentary system, the separation of powers, and the authority of the president will be redefined. 
The AKP also says it will continue efforts to secure macroeconomic and price stability. 
It set as objectives a national per capita income of $10,000 and $200 billion in exports by 2013. 
(Sabah, Zaman, Radikal - 25/06/07; Reuters, AP, AFP, CNN Turk - 24/06/07)
